tasks.description:
Create the single pure selector both recovery paths reuse, so the `remainingMs` math and the expired-exclusion rule live in exactly one place.

NEW FILE: apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/messaging/pending-interactions.ts

Export a `PendingInteractionDTO` type (a discriminated union by `type`) and a pure function:
```ts
import { SESSIONS } from '../../../../config/constants.js';
import type { InteractiveSession } from './interactive-handlers.js';

export type PendingInteractionDTO =
  | ({ id: string; type: 'approval'; startedAt: number; remainingMs: number } & ApprovalSnapshot)
  | ({ id: string; type: 'question'; startedAt: number; remainingMs: number } & QuestionSnapshot)
  | ({ id: string; type: 'elicitation'; startedAt: number; remainingMs: number } & ElicitationSnapshot);

/** Map a session's pending interactions to recovery DTOs, computing server-authoritative remainingMs and excluding expired (remainingMs <= 0) entries. */
export function listPendingInteractions(session: InteractiveSession, now: number): PendingInteractionDTO[] {
  const out: PendingInteractionDTO[] = [];
  for (const [id, pending] of session.pendingInteractions) {
    const remainingMs = Math.max(0, SESSIONS.INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS - (now - pending.startedAt));
    if (remainingMs <= 0) continue; // server has effectively auto-denied — never re-present
    out.push({ id, type: pending.type, startedAt: pending.startedAt, remainingMs, ...pending.snapshot } as PendingInteractionDTO);
  }
  return out;
}
```
Reuse the snapshot interfaces from task 1.1 (re-export them from interactive-handlers.ts or move them here and import — keep one source). `now` is injected (do not call `Date.now()` inside) so tests are deterministic. `INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS` is `10 * 60 * 1000` (config/constants.ts).

The boundary rule is `remainingMs <= 0` excludes — so an entry where `now - startedAt === INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS` yields `remainingMs === 0` and is EXCLUDED.

ACCEPTANCE TESTS (apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/messaging/__tests__/pending-interactions.test.ts):
- A session with one approval registered at `startedAt = 1000`, queried at `now = 1000 + 60_000`, returns one DTO with `remainingMs === INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS - 60_000` and the flattened snapshot fields. Purpose: remainingMs math.
- An entry where `now - startedAt === INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS` is EXCLUDED (boundary; remainingMs === 0). Purpose: expiry boundary is exclusive.
- An entry where `now - startedAt > INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS` is EXCLUDED. Purpose: expired never re-presented.
- Empty `pendingInteractions` returns `[]`. Purpose: none-case.
- Mixed approval + question + elicitation all map to their correct discriminated DTO shape. Purpose: all three types covered.

Implement the side-effect-free pull endpoint (recovery Path A) and wire it through the Transport interface.

1) ROUTE — apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts. Add a GET handler (place near the other session GETs; the file already imports `runtimeRegistry`, `parseSessionId`, `sendError`):
```ts
// GET /api/sessions/:id/pending-interactions - Recover active interactive prompts (Path A pull)
router.get('/:id/pending-interactions', async (req, res) => {
  const sessionId = parseSessionId(req.params.id);
  if (!sessionId) return sendError(res, 400, 'Invalid session ID', 'INVALID_SESSION_ID');
  const runtime = await runtimeRegistry.resolveForSession(sessionId);
  if (!runtime.hasSession(sessionId)) {
    return sendError(res, 404, 'Session not found', 'SESSION_NOT_FOUND');
  }
  const interactions = runtime.getPendingInteractions(sessionId);
  res.json({ interactions });
});
```
Returns `{ interactions: PendingInteractionDTO[] }`. `404` when the session is unknown (covers post-restart — the in-memory session is gone). `{ interactions: [] }` when a known session has no pending interactions. Read-only — never resolves anything. Register it in the OpenAPI registry the same way sibling session routes are registered (so `/api/docs` picks it up — full /api/docs entry text is task 3.5, but register the route + response schema `PendingInteractionsResponseSchema` here).

2) TRANSPORT INTERFACE — packages/shared/src/transport.ts. Add (near `getMessages`, ~195):
```ts
/** Fetch the session's currently-pending interactive prompts for recovery on (re)entry. */
getPendingInteractions(sessionId: string, cwd?: string): Promise<PendingInteractionsResponse>;
```

3) HTTP TRANSPORT — apps/client/src/layers/shared/lib/transport/session-methods.ts. Implement `getPendingInteractions` with a GET fetch to `/api/sessions/${sessionId}/pending-interactions` (mirror `getMessages` at ~101: same base URL/headers helper, same error handling). On a 404 return `{ interactions: [] }` (a session with no live server presence simply has nothing to recover — do not throw).

4) DIRECT TRANSPORT — apps/client/src/layers/shared/lib/direct-transport.ts. Implement `async getPendingInteractions(sessionId)` { return { interactions: this.services.runtime.getPendingInteractions(sessionId) }; } (mirror the in-process `approveTool` delegation at ~203).

5) MOCK — packages/test-utils/src/mock-factories.ts: `getPendingInteractions: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({ interactions: [] })`.

ACCEPTANCE TESTS (apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/sessions-interactive.test.ts — uses supertest + FakeAgentRuntime per .claude/rules/testing.md):
- GET on a session with a pending approval returns 200 `{ interactions: [<approval DTO with remainingMs>] }`. Drive it by having `FakeAgentRuntime.getPendingInteractions` return a known DTO (or register a real interaction on a real session-store-backed fixture). Purpose: happy path + remainingMs surfaced.
- GET excludes an expired interaction (selector already excludes; assert via a DTO list that omits it). Purpose: expiry exclusion observable through the endpoint.
- GET on an unknown session id returns 404 `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`. Purpose: unknown/post-restart case.
- GET on a known session with no interactions returns 200 `{ interactions: [] }`. Purpose: empty case.

Recovery Path B: on every persistent-stream (re)connect, replay non-expired pending interactions as their native events so live reconnect, background→foreground, and multi-surface clients recover without a manual refetch.

FILE: apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts — GET `/:id/stream` handler (~548-598).

Immediately AFTER the existing `sendSSEEvent(res, { type: 'sync_connected', data: { sessionId } })` (~567) and BEFORE/around the heartbeat + `watchSession` setup, iterate the recovery DTOs and write each as its native SSE event:
```ts
const pending = runtime.getPendingInteractions(sessionId); // [] if session unknown — safe
for (const it of pending) {
  if (it.type === 'approval') {
    res.write(`event: approval_required\ndata: ${JSON.stringify({ toolCallId: it.id, toolName: it.toolName, input: it.input, timeoutMs: SESSIONS.INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS, startedAt: it.startedAt, remainingMs: it.remainingMs, title: it.title, displayName: it.displayName, description: it.description, blockedPath: it.blockedPath, decisionReason: it.decisionReason, hasSuggestions: it.hasSuggestions })}\n\n`);
  } else if (it.type === 'question') {
    res.write(`event: question_prompt\ndata: ${JSON.stringify({ toolCallId: it.id, questions: it.questions, startedAt: it.startedAt, remainingMs: it.remainingMs })}\n\n`);
  } else {
    res.write(`event: elicitation_prompt\ndata: ${JSON.stringify({ interactionId: it.id, serverName: it.serverName, message: it.message, mode: it.mode, url: it.url, elicitationId: it.elicitationId, requestedSchema: it.requestedSchema, timeoutMs: SESSIONS.INTERACTION_TIMEOUT_MS, startedAt: it.startedAt, remainingMs: it.remainingMs })}\n\n`);
  }
}
```
The `data` shape MUST match the original in-band emit (so the existing client handlers parse it) PLUS `remainingMs`. Use the SAME event-name format the file already uses for sync events (`event: <type>\ndata: <json>\n\n`). Guard writes in try/catch like the heartbeat does. Expired interactions are already excluded by the selector (`getPendingInteractions`). This runs on EVERY (re)subscribe — EventSource auto-reconnect and tab refocus both re-open the stream, so no client-side trigger is needed.

Decide placement: doing it directly in the route handler (as above) keeps it co-located with `sync_connected`. If `session-broadcaster.ts` `registerClient`/`registerCallback` is the actual connect point for some clients, also emit there right after its `sync_connected` write (~133) using a callback the route passes, OR centralize by having the route write both. Prefer the route handler since `GET /:id/stream` writes `sync_connected` itself (~567) and owns `runtime`.

Imports: `SESSIONS` from config/constants is already imported in sessions.ts (used elsewhere) — confirm and reuse.

ACCEPTANCE TESTS (apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/sessions-interactive.test.ts using collectSseEvents/supertest):
- Open GET /:id/stream on a session with one pending approval → the client receives `sync_connected` THEN an `approval_required` event whose `data` includes `remainingMs` and matches the original emit shape. Purpose: Path B re-emit order + shape.
- An EXPIRED pending interaction is NOT re-emitted on connect. Purpose: expiry exclusion on Path B.
- A session with no pending interactions emits only `sync_connected` (no spurious interaction events). Purpose: no false positives.
- Question and elicitation pending interactions re-emit as `question_prompt`/`elicitation_prompt` respectively. Purpose: all three types on Path B.
